The Police in Kano State have arrested a 40-year-old man identified as Musbahu, for allegedly killing his three-year-old son. Spokesperson of the command, DSP Abdullahi Haruna, confirmed the incident to DAILY POST on Friday. He explained that the incident happened on Thursday at Mahaukaci Quarter in Gaya Local Government Area of Kano State. Haruna said the suspect was in police custody and will be charged to court after the investigation. Speaking to DAILY POST, the suspect, who admitted to have committed the crime, said he did it to save his son and himself from embarrassment as the child was born out of wedlock and he has no body to take care of him. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.